HEADWORD: Zeuglodon
<hw>Zeu"glo*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ the strap
or loop of a yoke + <?/, <?/, tooth.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A
genus of extinct Eocene whales, remains of which have been found in the
Gulf States. The species had very long and slender bodies and broad
serrated teeth. See <er>Phocodontia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zeuglodont</ent>⟦br⟧
